      <abstract>
        <p>Testimony of Zeev Scheck, the initiator of the Documentation campaign, Prague. Scheck
          describes the situation of children in the Theresienstadt ghetto. He is pointing out the
          role of Egon Redlich and Fredy Hirsch on the educational system of the ghetto, which he
          explains in detail. Most of the children in Terezín were placed into so-called children´s
          and youth homes, run by teachers and tutors, who looked after the mental and physical
          development of the children and offered them a purposeful use of their free time. Scheck
          also offers a brief statistic related to the children prisoners of the ghetto.</p>
      </abstract>


